    "Specifically, we specify a 2D center point for each class of data in the 8 classes and randomly add Gaussian noise based on those points to obtain the 2D coordinates of the input.",
    "The dataset visualization is shown on the left of Figure 3.",
    "We train a single hidden layer with 64 × 64 units using LoRA (r = 1), FourierFT (n = 128), and our proposed MaCP (n = 90) to fit the synthesized data.",
    "Notably, all methods require the same number of trainable parameters, making it a fair comparison.",
    "The experimental results, depicted on the right of Figure 3, highlight significant performance differences among these methods."
